# Landing Page Design System & Architecture

## Project Overview
Retro pixel-art gaming landing pages with unified design system. Two main pages: Home (Frame 1) and Registration (Frame 2) with consistent styling and responsive behavior.

## Design Aesthetic
- **Theme**: Retro 8-bit/16-bit pixel-art gaming
- **Background**: Pixelated jungle forest (`/public/landing/images/background.png`)
- **Font**: BoldPixels throughout all text elements
- **Colors**: Orange/yellow accents, white text, dark backgrounds
- **Style**: Pixelated, chunky, arcade-game inspired

## CSS Architecture (globals.css)
All styling centralized in unified CSS classes - NO inline styles except dynamic states:

### Layout Classes
- `.landing-page` - Main container with jungle background and flex centering
- `.landing-container` - Content wrapper with responsive max-widths
- `.landing-header` - Header section with centered text alignment

### Content Classes
- `.landing-title` - Dynamics Explorer title image (max-width responsive)
- `.landing-text` - Standard white text (1.25rem, BoldPixels font)
- `.landing-text-large` - Larger subtitle text (2rem, for single-line content)

### Button System
- `.landing-button` - Button image containers (BTN-orange.png, BTN-gray.png)
- `.landing-button-text` - Overlay text with responsive font sizes:
  - Phone (≤768px): 1.25rem
  - iPad (769px-1024px): 2rem
  - Web (≥1025px): 2rem

### Form System
- `.landing-form-container` - Transparent form wrapper (no background)
- `.landing-form-field` - Individual field containers with max-width
- `.landing-form-input` - Input styling with textfill-back.png background (60px height)
- `.landing-form-error` - Error message styling

## Responsive Breakpoints
Mobile-first approach with specific sizing:

### Phone (≤768px)
- Container: 320px max-width
- Title: 280px max-width  
- Buttons/Inputs: 280px max-width
- Button text: 1.25rem

### iPad (769px-1024px)
- Container: 550px max-width
- Title: 500px max-width
- Buttons/Inputs: 450px max-width
- Button text: 2rem

### Web (≥1025px)
- Container: 500px max-width
- Title: 450px max-width
- Buttons/Inputs: 400px max-width
- Button text: 2rem

## Component Structure

### Home Page (page.tsx)
```
- Dynamics Explorer title image (with embedded companial logo)
- Welcome text with line break after "gaming experience!"
- Start Your Adventure button (BTN-orange)
- View Leaderboard button (BTN-gray)
- NO footer text
```

### Registration Page (register/page.tsx)
```
- Dynamics Explorer title image (with embedded companial logo)
- "Register to start your conference challenge" subtitle (landing-text-large)
- Form with 3 inputs: Full Name, Email, Company (NO labels)
- Start Playing button (BTN-orange)
- NO footer text
```

### Leaderboard Page (leaderboard/page.tsx)
```
- Jungle background (same as landing pages)
- "Leaderboard" title (retro gaming style)
- Semi-transparent dark container with table
- Table with: Rank, Player, Company, Best Time, Date
- Medal icons for top 3 positions
- Three buttons using BTN-SM images: Play Again, Refresh, Home
- Responsive design matching landing page breakpoints
```

## Image Optimization
- Use Next.js `Image` component with required `width` and `height` props
- Add `priority` prop for above-the-fold images (Dynamics Explorer title)
- Handle aspect ratios in CSS, not inline styles
- Assets in `/public/landing/images/` and `/public/landing/fonts/`

## Key Design Principles
1. **No Duplicate Branding**: Companial logo only in Dynamics Explorer image
2. **Transparent Overlays**: Forms appear over jungle background
3. **Consistent Spacing**: Unified margin/padding system
4. **Pixelated Assets**: All images maintain retro aesthetic
5. **Responsive Font**: Button text scales with screen size
6. **Clean Forms**: No labels, placeholders indicate requirements

## Technical Implementation
- Next.js App Router with TypeScript
- React Hook Form with Zod validation
- Tailwind CSS for utilities (minimal usage)
- Unified CSS classes for all styling
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Font-face declaration for BoldPixels in globals.css

## File Organization
- `/src/app/` - Pages and layouts
- `/src/lib/` - Validation schemas and utilities  
- `/src/types/` - TypeScript definitions
- `/public/landing/` - All landing page assets
- `/supabase/functions/` - Serverless functions

## Development Guidelines
- Always use CSS classes, avoid inline styles
- Maintain responsive behavior across all breakpoints
- Keep design consistent between pages
- Use semantic HTML with proper accessibility
- Optimize images for performance
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles